info.additionalInfo:
note, the font specified in the CSS is Lato which is a google font, but this CSS solution assumes you have the Lato font on your own system - rather than loading it from google. You could change Lato to another font that you do have, or perhap add an @import line to this CSS (not tried)

e.g.
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Open+Sans');

style.css:
@-moz-document domain("mail.google.com"), domain("inbox.google.com") {

/* Global font and size */ 
    * {
    font-family:'Lato';
    font-size:13.3px!important;
}

 /* font/size when reading an OPENED MAIL */    
.adO.adP p,
.yq,
.yq *,
.gs *,
.b5.xJNT8d *,
.aV.editable {
    font-size:16px!important;
    line-height:1.5!important;
    }

 /* left column (labels list) font - line-height not doing much here */
    .n0 {
        color:#777777 !important;
    font-size:12.6px!important;
    line-height:1.0!important;
    }
  /* squash up the left column (labels list) a bit if you have lots of labels */
    .aim {margin-top:-5px;}
    
  /* this is for the QUICK REPLY BOX font (need to spec the font family again as the wildcard at top doesn't 'take' here) */
.LW-avf {  
    font-family:'Lato';
    font-size:17.5px!important;
    line-height:1.5!important;
    }  
    

}
